name: Decrement counter
Adjust the thermostat target temperatures
info:
Increment or decrement the target temperatures of the Living room thermostat.

Each the up or down buttons are pressed, a counter is incremented/decremented. Once 5 seconds has elapsed from the time of the last button-press, the current target will be retrieved and the new target calculated. The new target is then sent to the thermostat.

name: Reset the central_heating_manual switch
info: There is a manual overide switch to prevent Schedy switching to nighttime mode. This switch needs to be reset at midnight.

name: Control CH Boiler
info: Use the state of the "we need heat" virtual switch to control the Sheely switch that causes the boiler to fire.

name: Overview
info:
# Entities
- Each room has at least one radiator with a Danfoss TRV. Unfortunately, you cannot read the actual room temperature from the TRV, so
- Each room also has a temperature sensor
- Each room has a generic thermostat in HA which controls the state of:
- an input_boolean if the room needs heat
- Some rooms have up/down buttons in HA to increment/decrement the target temp

# Control loops
- Schedy is running in an Appdaemon addon to provide top level control of room set-points.
- A couple of rooms have a Node-Red flow that is triggered by the up/down buttons and adjust the room's 'thermostat'
- Each room then has a node-red flow to ensure the room's TRV mirrors the thermostat's set-point (with the option of adding an offset based on how closely the TRV's set-point matches that of the thermostat)
- An automation monitors the state of each room's "I need heat" input_boolean to decide if the House needs heat. (this allows the flexibility to add additional "rooms" or other reasons to switch the heating on)
- The last node-red flow then uses the state of the "we need heat" inut_boolean to control the boiler

name: How this flow works
info:
"Switch on Button ID" 
    selects an output using the value of msg.payload.payload.settings.id
Each value has a separate flow path
    Set msg.payload.event = "keyDown"
    Set msg.payload = "trigger"
    Process button-specific stuff
        Get the current saved value of the Switch
        If it's OFF, set msg.payload = "on"
        If it's ON, set payload = "off"
    Act on the new state
        e.g. send a message to esphome

When a button is pressed, and periodically
    The current state of a button is retrived from the flow variable
    this is used to build a new button label
    which is sent back to the Stream Deck button

name: Toggle state of Lock line
tuned
untuned
Config
func:
if (msg.payload == "untuned") {

    msg.background_opacity = "1.0"
    msg.background_color = "black"

    msg.icon_color = "red"
    msg.icon_opacity = "0.35"

    msg.one_text = "Untuned"
    msg.two_text = ""

    msg.text_one_color = "white"
    msg.text_two_color = "white"

    msg.font_one_size = "25px"
    msg.font_two_size = "15px"

    msg.text_one_anchor = "middle"
    msg.text_two_anchor = "middle"
    //Note:  possible anchors are: start, middle, end

    msg.one_x = "36"
    msg.two_x = "36"

    msg.one_y = "60"
    msg.two_y = "50"

}

else if (msg.payload == "tuned") {

    msg.background_opacity = "1.0"
    msg.background_color = "black"

    msg.icon_color = "green"

    msg.one_text = "Tuned"
    msg.two_text = ""

    msg.text_one_color = "yellow"
    msg.text_two_color = "white"

    msg.font_one_size = "25px"
    msg.font_two_size = "15px"

    msg.text_one_anchor = "middle"
    msg.text_two_anchor = "middle"
    //Note:  possible anchors are: start, middle, end

    msg.one_x = "36"
    msg.two_x = "36"

    msg.one_y = "60"
    msg.two_y = "50"

}

return msg;

name: set msg.payload
Filter own messages
All nodes need to have this group
info:
MQTT is used to communicate between node-red nodes
Each node messages on the topic `nodereed/<node>'
where <node> is the name of the source node.

All nodes receive meassages on `nodered/#`.
They then filter out those messages that originated
from their own node.
